summary:
Removable partial dentures adequately substitute for missing teeth without requiring a temporary resin bridge. No clinical indication supports using a temporary resin bridge when a partial denture is used instead of a permanent restoration.  

Final Answer:\boxed{A}

The summary focuses only on clinically significant insights related to why a temporary resin bridge isn't needed when a partial denture replaces a missing tooth — emphasizing functionality equivalence between treatments and lack of supporting need for interim bridging.

